ISLAMABAD, Mar 28 (APP): Federal Minister for Human Rights Dr:Shireen Mazari said on Sunday that Pakistan was well on track to be the 1st country in South Asia with a National Action Plan (NAP) on Business and Human Rights .
In her tweet Dr Mazari said that Ministry of Human Rights was accepting feedback and recommendations on the draft National Action Plan (NAP) till April 9.
